{
  "texts": [
    "Benchmarking datasets were sourced from ChEA3 2 for transcription factors and from KEA3 9 for kinases.",
    "To benchmark enrichment analysis performed with the constructed consensus gene set libraries, the rank of each transcription factor/kinase was identified using the Fisher's exact test p-value for each matching gene set in each benchmarking dataset.",
    "To generate ROC curves, we downsampled the negative class to the same size as the positive class to achieve class balance.",
    "ROC curves were then bootstrapped over 5000 iterations and the mean ROC and AUCs were reported.",
    "Since we are randomly downsampling the negative class, bootstrapping the curve over several thousand iterations ensures a more accurate depiction of the ability of the Rummagene transcription factor and kinases gene set libraries to accurately predict the perturbed transcription factor or kinase."
  ]
}